ZCZC OE72
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 222300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD BE CHARACTERISED BY A PAIR OF MAJOR LOWS IN TURN COMING
TO OCCUPY SIMILAR POSITIONS IN THE N ATLANTIC KEEPING A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE LARGELY OVER CONTINENTAL EUROPE THROUGHOUT. THE FIRST MAIN LOW IS
EXP SE ICELAND WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE NEAR 980 TO START THE PERIOD. THIS
LOW SHOULD FILL AND MOV INTO ARCTIC OCEAN INTO THE NEW WORKING WEEK AS ANOTHER
MAJOR AND COMPLEX LOW MOVS INTO THE N ATLANTIC IN ITS WAKE PERHAPS DEVELOPING
TWIN CENTRES IN THE AMBIT OF ICELAND BY THE END OF THE PERIOD. OCCASIONAL
STRG WINDS ARE LIKELY FOR MUCH OF ATLANTIC PORTPATRICK TO START THE PERIOD
EASING MONDAY AHEAD OF A NEW SWATHE OF SEV GALES ARRIVING IN WERN PORTPATRICK
INTO TUESDAY. WINDS PERHAPS BRIEFLY STORM IN THE FAR W EASING SEV GALE AND
THEN GALE IN TURN AS THEY PUSH BODILY EWARD THROUGH MUCH IF NOT ALL OF PORTPATRICK
TO MIDWEEK
